<HEADLINE>
FT  11 MAR 93 / Parliament and Politics: Fire safety laws set for review
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MINISTERS have ordered a review of Britain's 20-year-old fire safety
legislation, the Home Office confirmed last night.
The review will look at the issue of crown immunity, by which government and
royal buildings are exempt from prosecution even if fire precautions are
inadequate. Officials were unable to say when the review might end.
