<HEADLINE>
FT  11 MAR 93 / Parliament and Politics: Major plays down Scots water row
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE prime minister has insisted that no decision has been reached about
whether Scottish water should be privatised. On Tuesday, Mr Major sparked
opposition anger when he appeared to indicate that privatisation would go
ahead, telling MPs: 'I have no reason to doubt that water privatisation in
Scotland will be effective and efficient, as elsewhere.'
But in an interview in today's Scotsman newspaper, Mr Major says this should
have been qualified by a rider saying 'if implemented'.
He said: 'We are in the middle of a consultation period. We will finish the
consultation period. We will make a decision; it will take account of the
special Scottish dimension. That has always been the position.'
</TEXT>
