<HEADLINE>
FT  11 MAR 93 / Parliament and Politics: Motion attacks lease law
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SEVEN Labour MPs yesterday tabled an early day motion calling for the repeal
of a 'draconian' law under which anyone who signs a lease on commercial
premises can be forced to pay the rent owed by a subsequent tenant who
defaults.
The motion 'noted with dismay' the failure to implement the 1988 Law
Commission report in lifting 'the burden of medieval privity law'.
