FT  11 MAR 93 / London bus crews strike for a day
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
ABOUT ONE third of London's buses stayed in their depots yesterday as crews
staged a one-day protest strike over pay and conditions that a majority of
them have already accepted.
London Buses said no buses ran in some parts of the capital. Unions claimed
the strike - over pay cuts averaging Pounds 30 a week and extended hours -
was an 'overwhelming success'. They warned of another strike on Wednesday
unless management agreed to talks.
Mr Ollie Jackson, a TGWU transport union official, said his members had
signed new contracts and indicated that a prolonged dispute was unlikely.
