FT  11 MAR 93 / Outdated Army tanks for sale
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
PART OF the Army's outdated fleet of Chieftain tanks might be refitted for
sale to Pakistan, defence officials said.
Pakistan is considering buying up to 300 of the 850 Chieftains produced for
the Army in the late 1960s and early 1970s, according to the magazine Jane's
Defence Weekly. A consortium headed by GEC-Marconi is proposing an upgrade
package for the tanks.
Officials said any sale would probably be handled by private companies,
which would buy the tanks from the Ministry of Defence. They confirmed that
Pakistan was seen as a leading potential outlet.
