FT  11 MAR 93 / Canadian transport
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Sweeping changes in Canada's transport sector, including the privatisation
of Canadian National Railways have been proposed by the National
Transportation Act Review Commission, writes Robert Gibbens in Montreal.
Under the proposals, foreigners will be allowed to own 49 per cent of a
Canadian airline, up from the present 25 per cent, and all transport
subsidies will be phased out. Canada's central bank rate declined 23 basis
points yesterday to 5.66 per cent from 5.89 per cent a week earlier. The
total decline since late last November is now 316 basis points and the
Canadian dollar has weakened after two weeks of continuous strength. The
banks were expected to drop their prime lending rates to 6.25 per cent, a
20-year low.
