<HEADLINE>
FT  11 MAR 93 / Yemen bomb hits UK embassy
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A bomb exploded outside the British embassy in the Yemeni capital Sanaa
yesterday, damaging the compound's perimeter wall but causing no injuries, a
British official said, Reuter reports.
He said the 'small explosive device' went off in the early hours of the
morning.
The US and German missions have been bombed recently.
