<HEADLINE>
FT  10 MAR 93 / UK Company News: Maple Leaf moves ahead 16%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Maple Leaf Foods, the food processing group 56 per cent owned by Hillsdown,
reported profits of CDollars 69.2m (Pounds 38.8m), or 86 cents a share, for
1992, up 16 per cent, writes Robert Gibbens.
Sales were CDollars 2.8bn, down slightly reflecting the group's withdrawal
from the beef business.
Fourth-quarter profit from continuing operations was CDollars 17.8m, or 22
cents a share, against CDollars 19.4m, or 25 cents a share, on sales little
changed at CDollars 739m.
The company said disposals, heavy investment in facilities and rising
efficiency had created a sound base for future growth in Canada and the US.
